---
description: Security rules for the sample todo app
alwaysApply: true
---

- Never write, log, or echo secrets, API keys, or production credentials in code or output
- No `eval`, `send`, or `public_send` on user input
- No `html_safe` or `raw` on untrusted user input -- always let Rails auto-escape
- Use parameterized queries and ActiveRecord methods; never string-interpolate into SQL
- Do not disable CSRF protection (`skip_before_action :verify_authenticity_token`)
- Do not disable mass assignment protection or use `permit!`
- Do not commit `.env` files, `master.key`, or credential keys to version control
- Validate and sanitize all user input at the controller/model boundary
